<br>
Pets are Tanks.<br>
<br>
In the past, tanks have complained about our pets being overpowered sometimes, but it was situational.  Our pets could never keep agro like a real tank could, or had the same hp and ac of a real tank.  You never heard a group or raid going after a named say, they didnt need a tank, because they had a mage pet for that.<br>
<br>
I have never played a ank, even going back as far as 1980's and playing D&amp;D.  So, there is no envy here, but feeling sorry for tanks.<br>
<br>
I feel sorry, that even with dc, tanks were getting left behind on being needed.  Now with these new charmed pets, why would a group or raid want a tank with 7k hp, when they can have one now with 20, 30, 40k or more hp, and hits in the hundreds.<br>
<br>
What has been said in the past alot, is that pets are great to have and help out, but they should't replace a tank with one pet.  Now, one pet is replacing 2 - 3 groups?  Sorry, but to me, that seems like god mode in some of the old games I left, to come play EQ.<br>
<br>
Hopefully, they will fix it, so that it is still useful, but not be, where EQ has only enchanters playing the game anymore. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Times New roman;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gandolph / Kozymo</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
