<br>
Also remember that the tanks efficiency is based on the efficiency of CH. As more PoP armors become available to tanks and their HP gets close to 10k so a 7.5K CH actually heals 7.5K HP, rather than 4 or 5k which is probably the norm atm, then using a charmed pet to tank holds no real advantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pissed1vi2soe@themagicianstower>Pissed1VI2SOE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 565<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 7:07:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=447.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Charm 'nerf' and it's faults.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> they didnt need a tank, because they had a mage pet for that <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
