<br>
I played an enchanter for over 2 years before finally giving up in disgust in the luclin era and I switched to a cleric since then. So I have a certain experience with the class and I am wary about some of the suggested fixes. My perspective is mostly about raids, because this is where issues will arise for the class if charm is nerfed to the point of no longer being worth the risk.<br>
<br>
There is one reason why enchanters are 100% fine and maybe overpowered in the PoP expansion and it's because charm is working. It's the single reason why enchanters stack in most raids in PoP. Pre PoP the mobs were either too high for the old charm spells, too resistant, or just hard coded immune when they weren't. The enchanter ability to charm wasn't underpowered back then. Worse; it was (mostly) *useless*.<br>
<br>
Now I know mezz is working again and it's also a good change. But mezz *is* situational. There is a few encounters where it can make the difference between victory and defeat. Most of the time we tell our enchanters to keep a charmed pet instead of worrying about mezz and we tank split the adds - or root them if we have room. Help with faster clearings this way. With PoP and many areas the size of a football field there are many adequate alternatives to mezz. Harmony being one of them, and far superior and that, given that most of the zones are outdoor.<br>
<br>
What is certainly true, is that without charms enchanters are incomplete. Buffs aren't a balance factor. It's something that is easily botted. Classes are balanced by their active combat role, and the enchanter's role in PoP is overwhelmingly centered on charm. If you disable charm, or nerf it to a point where it's no longer worth it's risk - because there is a varying amount of risk depending on the area - then you will unbalance the class the other way.<br>
<br>
Now I do admit that there are some problems with charm and PoP. <br>
<br>
The problem I do have with charm (and PoP in general) is the experience discrepancy between classes that can solo efficiently (enchanters, druids, necros and maybe 1 or 2 others), and the classes that are group dependant.<br>
<br>
How do you lure an enchanter to join your group to provide essential melee support when he can get so much better xp soloing or duoing? Answer, you can't because he's making far better xp soloing, and he doesn't want to be bottled up in the soporiphic role of slower/buff dispenser. <br>
<br>
And since slow is essential for any form of non charm melee engagement in PoP, there goes a significant portion of your slowers. <br>
<br>
Basically it's hard to get an enchanter to group, because he's playing a different (and superior) game when it's coming to grouping and getting experience. This is wrong. <br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
What I am trying to say is that yes, we have to admit there is a problem, and a serious discrepancy in the experience game that has to be solved. <br>
<br>
But be wary of any solutions that would make charm not worth the risk anymore. Right now the enchanter's place in the raiding game is dependant on charm being worth the risk, and the support required to maintain these pets - because you don't find PoS frogs or PoV golems type mobs for every raid.<br>
<br>
I think the right place of charm is in a setting where either everyone can solo (why not?), or in another where you need more than the resources of just the enchanter to maintain and use the pet at the effectivenes we currently see. There's nothing wrong if you use a 400 dps pet but need resources from several other players to mitigate the risk created by charm, because then it's not really one player doing that damage, but several.<br>
<br>
That's my idea of how it should be. What changes to make to move from the current situation to what I think it &quot;should&quot; be? To be honest - I am not sure. The fastest fix would be to make all PoP mobs summon, but it would kill the ability to solo for anyone but shamans, and I am not sure it's a good idea. But it would certainly make charm more of a group thing.<br>
<br>
Another partial fix would be to modify the game mechanics so that everyone can solo for some xp if they can't find a group.<br>
<br>
