<br>
First, not every mage beyond 60th level is 65th level, hard as that may be to believe.<br>
<br>
Second, not every mage has access to the resources to obtain <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Call of the Archmage</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, either guild, flags or funds.<br>
<br>
Third, there are not enough appropriate camps, i.e. with charmable summoned mobs, to support every post-<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>60</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mage that wants to solo.<br>
<br>
It is extremely obvious to anyone that does the math that any mage who <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">can</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> solo with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Call of the Archmage</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> will do extremely well.  It does not necessarily follow that all post-60 mages solo extremely well.<br>
